Ticket 1: Add runnable test scripts (no other changes)

Outcome

Engineers can run the existing vitest suite locally via package scripts.

Why

Tests exist but there is no script to run them, increasing regression risk.

Evidence

package.json has scripts for dev/build/preview only (package.json lines 5-9).

vitest is already installed (package.json dependency list includes vitest, line 49).

Existing tests: src/app/tests/delete.test.ts (for example lines 1-116+).

Scope
In scope

Update package.json only by adding two scripts:

test: vitest run

test:watch: vitest

Out of scope (non-negotiable)

No other package.json changes.

No changes to app code.

No changes to existing tests.

No new tests.

No coverage configuration.

No CI workflows or quality gates.

No dependency changes.

Implementation

Edit package.json scripts block to include:

"test": "vitest run"

"test:watch": "vitest"

Acceptance criteria

npm run test runs vitest in run mode and exits with a non-zero code on failure.

npm run test:watch starts vitest in watch mode.

Existing tests execute under these scripts without requiring any additional configuration changes.

Verification steps

npm run test

npm run test:watch

Effort

S

Risk of change

Low

Claude risk check

No open questions remain.

No “nice to have” follow-ons are permitted in this ticket.

The only acceptable diff is package.json adding the two scripts.